li.p:
The graph shows the result of shifting f(x) to the left by 3 units, so we just add 3 to the input of f(x), giving us: 
                y \amp= f(x+3)
                \amp= (x+3)^2 - \sqrt{x+3}

setup.pg-code:
$h1 = Real(random(1, 9, 1));
$h2 = Real(random(-9, -1, 1));
$k1 = Real(random(-5, 5, 1));
$k2 = Real(random(-5, 5, 1));
$f = Compute("(x - $h1)^2 + $k1");
$g = Compute("(x - $h2)^2 + $k2");
